# Common DevOps Examples

### Monitor application logs

```bash
tail -f application.log
```

### View a system log

```bash
less /var/log/syslog
```

### Count log entries

```bash
wc -l access.log
```

### Compare configuration files

```bash
diff nginx.conf nginx.conf.backup
```

### Display a configuration file

```bash
cat app.conf
```

---

# Safety Tips

✅ Use `pwd` before deleting files.

✅ Use `ls` before running `rm`.

✅ Verify files before deleting them.

✅ Use `tail -f` to monitor logs instead of reopening them repeatedly.

✅ Use `less` instead of `cat` for very large files.

⚠ Never run:

```bash
rm -rf /
```

or

```bash
sudo rm -rf /
```

unless you intentionally want to destroy the system.

